The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on topic modeling using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates the quality of topic and document representations using information retrieval (IR) and generalization (perplexity), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a transfer learning approach, which involves using pre-trained models and knowledge from other domains, indicating that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DL (Deep Learning) categories.
